# All lab steps let's go!

1. Create Spoke 2 Site
2. Onboard SSR2 (Spoke 2)
   - Adopt
   - Assign to Spoke 2 Site (and enable management. How do I do this via the API?)
  
3. Set SSR2 DNS servers to 8.8.8.8
4. Create WAN1 on interface ge-0/0/0 (Spoke2_INET)(What is this called on the SSR?)
    - DHCP (default)
    - Source NAT interface (default)
  
5. Ping the SSR2 WAN interface (Can the API kick this off?)
6. Create LAN
    - Create network
        - Subnet 10.88.88.0 /24
        - Access to MIST Cloud: Disabled
        - Advertised via Overlay: Disabled
    - Set network to interface ge-0/0/3 ( Spoke2_LAN )
        - IP Config
        - 10.88.88.1/24
7. Ping test from Desktop2 -> SSR2 (10.88.88.1)
8. Configure Traffic Steering
    - Name: Internet
    - Strategy: Ordered
    - Add Path:
            - Type: WAN
            - Name: WAN1